      "content": "i hear you, but \"small steps\" feel so patronizing when the house is literally on fire. it feels like trying to fix a leak in a dam that has already collapsed. if the planet is just going to become unlivable anyway, why bother with the struggle? why bother with the noise and the pain of trying to survive in a world that's basically a corpse? it just seems like a lot of wasted energy for a dead end.",
